main event: A UFO was observed traveling in a Northeasterly direction in Columbus, Ohio on September 19, 1962 around 2:50 AM.
interesting points: The object was traveling on an Easterly course.
There is insufficient data for analysis of the object, as it could have been an aircraft or an ECHO satellite.
The report includes a handwritten sketch or drawing of the observed object, which appears to be an elongated, elliptical shape.
The report was filed on September 14, 1962, which is a few days after the sighting.
The report indicates that no photographs were taken of the observed object.
